name: Gov. Pete Ricketts
tweet: Nebraska’s Ukrainian community shared an important reminder today.   Another thing we can do for Ukraine: Pray.  https://t.co/DhhGl6cvap

name: Gov. Pete Ricketts
tweet: You can read more about the statewide effort and see a list for ways Nebraskans can donate to Ukraine here:   https://t.co/dxiqKhyp4n

name: Gov. Pete Ricketts
tweet: Thanks to @IAGovernor Reynolds for working to get IA and NE's donations to Ukraine. Soon, those defending their homeland will have more protective gear-- straight from the Heartland.

name: Gov. Pete Ricketts
tweet: Our state agencies worked to to collect donations of out-of-warranty body armor from state and local law enforcement across NE. Some officers even generously donated individually.    In total, 550 pieces of protective equipment were loaded onto a plane bound for Ukraine.

name: Gov. Pete Ricketts
tweet: Ukrainians have bravely withstood Russia’s unprovoked invasion for more than a month. As the Ukrainian people defend their homeland, they have an immense need for protective gear.   At a news conference today, I shared that Nebraska has stepped up to help meet this need.

name: Gov. Pete Ricketts

name: Gov. Pete Ricketts
tweet: Tune in at 2:30 to my Facebook livestream as I highlight statewide efforts to support Ukraine

name: Gov. Pete Ricketts
tweet: However, the Chair of the Judiciary Committee is holding 17 reasonable policies hostage to push four soft-on-crime measures that would have a large, negative impact on public safety.  More here:  https://t.co/X1POUGY5Aj

name: Gov. Pete Ricketts
tweet: The NELeg has the opportunity pass smart criminal justice reforms to enhance public safety & benefit all Nebs. These changes will allow us to better manage our inmate population & provide modern resources to prepare them for life after prison—without compromising public safety.

name: Gov. Pete Ricketts
tweet: ICYMI: the February jobs report is out. NE still has the lowest unemployment rate in the U.S.  With over 1 mil employed, we have 16,252 more Nebraskans in the workforce than we did pre-COVID.   If you’re looking for opportunity, the Good Life is calling!   https://t.co/F12vG3U8WL

name: Gov. Pete Ricketts
tweet: Just visited McLean Beef in York. Nebraska’s locally owned businesses are the pinnacle of Nebraska grit. Thanks to the McLean family for showing me around!   Next time you’re in York, check out their restaurant, market, or 24/7 meat vending machine. (You heard that right!)  https://t.co/sUbV5HdBvj

name: Gov. Pete Ricketts
tweet: Today, I’m out on another tour for #Agweek. AGP, in Hastings, is the largest soybean processor west of the Mississippi. Each year AGP crushes about 65mil bushels of soybeans- half go toward biofuels. They’re expanding to David City, which will only #growNE’s ability to produce.  https://t.co/oyybZaqs9P

name: Gov. Pete Ricketts
tweet: Increased ethanol production will also reduce U.S. dependence on foreign oil immediately. NE is the #2 ethanol producer in the U.S., with a capacity to produce 2.6bil gallons a year. If @POTUS allows for year-round use of higher ethanol blends, NE will be ready to fill that need.

name: Gov. Pete Ricketts
tweet: Yesterday, I spoke with leaders in Nebraska’s ethanol industry about the pivotal role biofuels can play to save drivers money at the pump, reduce toxic emissions, and create opportunities for farm families here in our state.  https://t.co/nlHOY0iCvp

name: Gov. Pete Ricketts
tweet: This week, our Legislature is considering pro-life legislation that will take effect the moment Roe v. Wade is undone.   Read more in my weekly column:  https://t.co/0ZNiZRBQ7d

name: Gov. Pete Ricketts
tweet: SCOTUS' decision on Roe v. Wade gave false credibility to their movement. But in less than four months, SCOTUS could finally overturn Roe.  Their ruling could return the ability to regulate abortion to the states. If it does, Nebraska must be ready to protect the unborn.

name: Gov. Pete Ricketts
tweet: For decades, the abortion industry has tried their best to normalize a culture of death, where the most vulnerable among us have fallen victim to the lie that one person’s so-called right to privacy trumps the right of another to live.

name: Gov. Pete Ricketts
tweet: Final stop today is Seitec Genetics. Headquartered in Fremont, Seitec supplies hybrid seeds designed to increase crop yields in Nebraska and beyond.   They’re a great example of Ag innovation in NE. #AgDay #AgWeek  https://t.co/G15RIEdaOw

name: Gov. Pete Ricketts
tweet: Next stop: Wahoo Meat Locker. It’s a proud family-owned and operated custom meat processing company that doubles as a retail store.   The buy local, farm-to-plate movement has helped put places like Wahoo Meat Locker on the map.  #AgDay #agweek  https://t.co/8euRaUGe6u

name: Gov. Pete Ricketts
tweet: Beauty View Dairy Farms is a family owned and operated dairy, beef, and row crop farm in Wahoo that’s been around since 1877. Look for their cheese curds in stores!  https://t.co/Ocw2E35Wia

name: Gov. Pete Ricketts
tweet: Happy Ag Week – and International Ag Day! Throughout this week, I'll be visiting a few Nebraska farms and businesses to highlight the importance of agriculture in our state. #agweek

name: Gov. Pete Ricketts
tweet: Yesterday, Susanne and I had the honor to worship with the Assumption Ukrainian Catholic Church in Omaha and pray for our brothers and sisters in Ukraine.   Nebraska stands with Ukraine against Russia’s aggression. We will continue to explore ways to show that support.  https://t.co/Z04OsF1WcX

name: Gov. Pete Ricketts
tweet: The NE Legislature is about to take another vote on LB1073.   A vote for this bill is a vote for big government socialism in NE. This is @POTUS attempt to pay people's rent for 3 years, no COVID impact needed.   Call your State Senator now to urge them to vote "no" on LB1073.

name: Gov. Pete Ricketts
tweet: As the NELeg considers how to spend ARPA funds, I’m encouraging them to prioritize our kids. Remote learning didn’t meet the needs of all students during the pandemic.  Educational recovery accounts empower families to help their kids get back on track.  https://t.co/UcZmci4Kon

name: Gov. Pete Ricketts

name: Gov. Pete Ricketts
tweet: There are now 12k more Nebraskans employed in our workforce than there were in Jan 2020—before the pandemic began.   Thanks to the hard work of Nebraskans, we’ve grown our state despite facing the greatest public health emergency of the past century.   https://t.co/2rRpWli6Ba

name: Gov. Pete Ricketts
tweet: Great leadership from Senator Brewer, whose constitutional carry bill, LB 773, advanced in the NE Legislature today. Current events remind us just how important the right to self-defense is to a free society  #2A

name: Gov. Pete Ricketts
tweet: Nomi Health has been a tremendous partner with the State. In a time of emergency and uncertainty, @nomihealth helped us successfully launch TestNebraska to provide quick, affordable COVID testing to more than one million Nebraskans.   https://t.co/klDtWif4En

name: Gov. Pete Ricketts
tweet: Today, the same Legislature voted for big government socialism in Nebraska.   LB 1073 seeks to force Nebraska to take a second round of ERAP funds— three years of rent subsidies that are not tied to any emergency.
